@node "Intro" "Introduction"
@next "Requi"

 Door Runner is a program that allows you to code doors for MAX's BBS (and
Paragon/StarNET compatibles BBSs) in any language, whether or not they
support Message Ports.
 Due to the way Door Runner works it is very flexible and can adapt as MAXs
adapts.  If someone writes a patch that gives MAXs a new door command then
Door Runner automatcally can use this command without modification, all that
needs to be done is a procedure has to be written for each language that
tells Door Runner of this new door command.

@endnode

@node "Requi" "Requirements"
@next "Insta"
@prev "Intro"

 Door Runner and your doors will require OS 2.0+

@endnode

@node "Insta" "Installation"
@next "Using"
@prev "Requi"

 The DoorRunner executable MUST reside in C:
 Read an individual Door's documentation to find out how to install that
particular door.

@endnode

@node "Using" "Using Door Runner"
@next "Autho"
@prev "Insta"

 Once you have coded your door you execute it as a normal door and aslong
as the DoorRunner executable is in C: and you have T: assigned then all
will work like a dream.
 As an example, if you have just compiled your door as Doors:EgDoor then run
it from MAXs like this;

Key  Func Extra  Lo Acc  Hi Acc  Filename
M    34   0      0       10000   Doors:EgDoor

 To write your own doors go to the bottom of the source file for your
language and you will see a comment saying "YOUR CODE GOES HERE", delete
all the example code for the example door and insert your own, then compile
as usual.
 In some languages you may be able to include the source file or compile it
as an external module etc, I leave this upto you so that you may change the
function names (but not distribute changed copies) to suit yourself.

@endnode

