@node "Regis" "How To Register"
@next "Users"
@prev "Histo"

 Door Runner is made available under the concept of Share-Ware, but with
a difference.  Share-Ware software authors often release `crippled'
versions of their products, i.e. these programs do not support the same
functionality as the registered versions you get when sending monetary
contributions to the authors. It all comes down to `pay for the software
you are using' in Share-Ware terms. With Door Runner, there is no
`crippled' test release which you can try for a limited time, I just appeal
to ever users conscience to register.  It took me many hours of hard work to
learn how MAXs operates and to design a system as flexible as Door Runner,
and a little money for my time is not a lot to ask.

 Registration costs 5uk pounds or 10US dollars, no other currencies are
accepted (sorry).

