 MAXShowFile(filename:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Displays the textfile filname.

 Inputs:   filename - The name of the file to display

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E16" ""
@next "E17"
@prev "E15"

 MAXFindFile(filename:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Finds if file filename is currently accessible by the system.
           Handles '*' & joker '?' search templates.

 Inputs:   filename - Filename to search for

 Returns:  FALSE -> File locked or not found
           TRUE  -> Ok (i think this means the file was found but I
                    haven't been able to check this)

@endnode

@node "E17" ""
@next "E18"
@prev "E16"

 MAXReturnFile(buffer:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Returns name of file found with MAXFindFile if a wildcard search
           template was used.

 Inputs:   buffer - A buffer that gets filled with filename

 Returns:  Nothing

 Note:     Must be called directly after MAXFindFile, well before any other
           door commands, if you want to know the filename because
           otherwise the variable used will become corrupted.

@endnode

@node "E18" ""
@next "E19"
@prev "E17"

 MAXEditFile(filename:PTR TO CHAR, maxlines:LONG)

 Function: Edits file filename.

 Inputs:   filename - Filename to edit
           maxlines - maximum nunnber of lines file can be

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

 Note:     I can't get this to work.  I think it's a bug in MAXs.

@endnode

@node "E19" ""
@next "E20"
@prev "E18"

 MAXGetUserNum(item:LONG)

 Function: Returns numerical information about current user.

 Inputs:   item - Can be any 1 of the following:
           1    - User's access level
           2    - Expert mode (Paragon/StarNET only)
           3    - Net credits (Paragon/StarNET only)
           4    - Number of calls
           5    - Calls to system
           6    - Graphics mode (Paragon/StarNET only)
           7    - Minutes remaining
           8    - Screen columns (Paragon/StarNET only)
           9    - Screen rows

 Outputs:  Relevant information about current User

@endnode

@node "E20" ""
@next "E21"
@prev "E19"

 MAXGetUserStr(item:LONG,buffer:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Returns alphanumeric information about current user.

 Inputs:   item   - Can be any 1 of the following:
             1    - User's Name
             2    - User's Password
             3    - User's Address
             4    - User's City (Paragon/StarNET only)
             5    - User's State (paragon/StarNET only)
             6    - User's Postal/Zip code (Paragon/StarNET only)
             7    - Path to the doors
             8    - Main BBS path
             9    - Date
            10    - Time
           100    - User's Phone number
           101    - User's Computer
           102    - User's Comment
           buffer - A buffer that gets filled with User's data

 Outputs:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E21" ""
@next "E22"
@prev "E20"

 MAXSetAccess(newaccess:LONG)

 Function: Changes the user's access level.

 Inputs:   newaccess - The user's new access level

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E22" ""
@next "E23"
@prev "E21"

 MAXSetUserStr(item:LONG,newstr:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Sets alphanumeric information about current user.

 Inputs:   item   - Can be any 1 of the following:
             1    - User's Name
             2    - User's Password
             3    - User's Address
             4    - User's City (Paragon/StarNET only)
             5    - User's State (Paragon/StarNET only)
             6    - User's Postal/Zip code (Paragon/StarNET only)
             7    - Path to the doors
             8    - Main BBS path
             9    - Date
            10    - Time
           100    - User's Phone number
           101    - User's Computer
           102    - User's Comment
           newstr - a string containing the new alphanumerical information

 Outputs:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

