 MAXShowGfxFile(filename:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Displays the graphic text file filename with correct extension
           based on User's graphics mode.

 Inputs:   filename - The name of the file to display

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

 Note:     Paragon/StarNET only.

@endnode

@node "E26" ""
@next "E27"
@prev "E25"

 MAXAlterTime(timechange:LONG)

 Function: Adds/Subtracts timechange to user's minutes remaining.  If +ve
           then Add, if -ve then Subtract.  

 Inputs:   timechange - The number of mnutes to Add/Subtract

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E27" ""
@next "E28"
@prev "E26"

 MAXMenuFunction(command:LONG, extra:LONG, string:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Performs BBS menu function command. EG 24 = Download.

 Inputs:   command - The BBS menu command (see MAXs/Paragon docs)
           extra   - The extra field, like in the menu editor
           string  - The filename field, like in the menu editor (MAX 80
                     chars)

 Returns:  Resultcode from relevant function (ignore usually)

 Note:     NOT Paragon/StarNET!
           Acording to the official docs only commands 0-33 are supported
           but i managed to get a number of them at random working such as
           Raw Download (37) etc. so all i can suggest is you try them out
           and see.  Command 34 WILL NOT work as MAXs can't handle doors
           running other doors.

@endnode

@node "E28" ""
@next "E29"
@prev "E27"

 MAXNoWaitHotKey(message:PTR TO CHAR, buffer:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Prints message to Local Screen & Modem and prompts for hotkey
           input from user, but does not wait for response, returns
           immediately.

 Inputs:   message - The message you want to be printed (MAX 80 chars)
           buffer  - A buffer that gets filled with the hotkey pressed or
                     NULL if no hotkey pressed

 Returns:  0 -> Local sysop hit key
           1 -> Remote user hit key

 Note:     NOT Paragon/StarNET!

@endnode

@node "E29" ""
@next "E30"
@prev "E28"

 MAXSetPageLight(condition:LONG)

 Function: Toggles the SysOp page 'light' on the Local Screen.

 Inputs:   condition - Set to 1 for On & 0 for Off

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E30" ""
@next "E31"
@prev "E29"

 MAXAutoInsert(asciicode:LONG,buffer:PTR TO CHAR)

 Function: Parses autoinserts.

 Inputs:   asciicode - the asciicode of the desired autoinsert.
                       eg 119 = w = Current Baudrate.
           buffer    - A buffer that gets filled with the parsed autoinsert

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok

@endnode

@node "E31" ""
@prev "E30"

 MAXShutDown()

 Function: Tells MAXs that we no longer require door functions.

 Returns:  FALSE -> Error
           TRUE  -> Ok (you can quit now)

 Note:     After calling MAXShutDown you may NOT call any more of the
           functions in this file.  If you do nothing will happen (so there
           is not much point in trying).  Unlike the AMOS extension these
           functions will not crash if you try the above :-)

@endnode
